<h2>Keyboard Mapping and Types</h2>
<h3>Keyboard Mapping</h3>
<p>
Default the PC key 'Ins' is mapped to the Elf 2000 'In' button/switch. F12 is mapped to the Elf 2000 'Run' button/switch, if the CPU is stopped it will start and when running it will stop, stop mode is indicated in the emulated window title. See also <a href="KeyMappingMain.htm">Key Mapping</a> and <a href="MainFunctionKeys.htm">Function and Hot Keys</a>.
</p>
<h3>Keyboard Types</h3>
<p>
To select the specific Elf 2000 keyboard type use the choice button 'Keyboard'. Currently 3 types are supported: 
</p>
<h4>
PS2 Keyboard: 
</h4>
<p>
Keyboard type operating with serial communication using control characters. Needed for running Elf 2000 with intel 8275 video.
</p>
<h4>
PS2 + JP4: 
</h4>
<p>
Same as above except the escape sequences are used for the keypad application mode.
</p>
<h4>
Hex Keyboard: 
</h4>
<p>
Only 1 hex keypad is supported.
</p>
<p>
To change and view the hex keypad to PC key mapping select the 'Key Map' button, see also chapter <a href="KeyMappingMain.htm">Key Mapping</a>
</p>
</BODY>
